name: hurricane-ivan-aerial-photography-high-resolution-imagery-of-the-florida-panhandle-and-surround
notes: The imagery posted on this site is of the Florida panhandle and surrounding regions after Hurricane Ivan made landfall. The regions photographed range from Gulf Port, Mississippi, to Fort Walton Beach, Florida. The aerial photograph missions were conducted by the NOAA Remote Sensing Division the day after Ivan made landfall, September 17 and concluded September 20. The images were acquired from an altitude of 7,500 feet, using an Emerge/Applanix Digital Sensor System (DSS). A total of 2,000 aerial images were obtained during this time period, with more than 1,300 images available to view online and download.
